measure.CatchLine: Limits terminations and rent increases for three years after tenants' housing is withdrawn from publicly supported housing.
measure.MeasureSummary:
Limits terminations and rent increases for three years after tenants' housing is withdrawn from publicly supported housing. 
	Requires owners or landlords to provide notice to new tenants and applicants during notice period before withdrawal from publicly supported housing. 
	Allows Housing and Community Services Department to record extension of affordability restrictions for publicly supported housing if property owner misses certain deadlines. Allows department to record right of first refusal if no qualified purchaser makes an offer. 
	Makes other amendments to publicly supported housing preservation program. 
	Declares emergency, effective on passage.
measure.RelatingToFull: Relating to preservation of publicly supported housing; and declaring an emergency.
measure.RelatingTo: Relating to preservation of publicly supported housing; and declaring an emergency.
